Constructor Detail

Plotter

public Plotter(double[][] dataX,
               double[][] dataY,
               java.lang.String title,
               java.lang.String titleX,
               java.lang.String titleY,
               java.lang.String type,
               boolean xLine,
               boolean yLine,
               boolean uLine)
Create a new Plotter JPanel and save information about the data values and the labeling.

Parameters:
dataX - a double[][] containing X data values for a number(dataX.length) of curves
dataY - a double[][] containing Y data values for a number(dataY.length) of curves
title - the title of the data plot
titleX - the title of the x axis.
titleY - the title of the y axis.
xLine - the flag specifies if x = 0 line is required.
yLine - the flag specifies if y = 0 line is required.
uLine - the flag specifies if unit slope line is required.
type - format of presentation: "dots", "line" or "both".
Method Detail

paintComponent

public void paintComponent(java.awt.Graphics gc)
Repaint the JPanel with all the desired information. The plot includes x and y axes, a data curve, labels showing the max x and y values, and a title label.

Parameters:
gc - the graphics context provided by the system.
